h501.definition: from {{h410}} and {{h6213}}; God has made; Elasah, the name of four Israelites; Elasah, Eleasah.

h502.definition: a primitive root, to associate with; hence, to learn (and causatively to teach); learn, teach, utter.

h503.definition: denominative from {{h505}}; causative, to make a thousandfold; bring forth thousands.

h504.definition: from {{h502}}; a family; also (from the sense of yoking or taming) an ox or cow; family, kine, oxen.

h505.definition: prop, the same as {{h504}}; hence (the ox's head being the first letter of the alphabet, and this eventually used as a numeral) a thousand; thousand.

h507.definition: the same as {{h505}}; Eleph, a place in Palestine; Eleph.

h508.definition: from {{h410}} and {{h6466}}; God (is) act; Elpaal, an Israelite; Elpaal.

h509.definition: a primitive root; to press; urge.

h510.definition: probably from {{h408}} and {{h6965}}; a non-rising (i.e. resistlessness); no rising up.

h511.definition: from {{h410}} and {{h7069}}; God has obtained; Elkanah, the name of several Israelites; Elkanah.

h512.definition: patrial from a name of uncertain derivation; an Elkoshite or native of Elkosh; Elkoshite.

h513.definition: probably from {{h410}} and a masculine form of {{h8435}} (compare {{h8434}}); God (is) generator; Eltolad, a place in Palestine; Eltolad.

h514.definition: or (more properly) אֶלְתְּקֵה; of uncertain derivation; Eltekeh or Elteke, a place in Palestine; Eltekeh.

h515.definition: from {{h410}} and {{h8626}}; God (is) straight; Eltekon, a place in Palestine; Eltekon.

h516.definition: from {{h408}} and {{h7843}}; 'Thou must not destroy'; probably the opening words to a popular song; Al-taschith.

h517.definition: a primitive word; a mother (as the bond of the family); in a wide sense (both literally and figuratively [like father]); dam, mother, × parting.

h518.definition: a primitive particle; used very widely as demonstrative, lo!; interrogative, whether?; or conditional, if, although; also Oh that!, when; hence, as a negative, not; (and, can-, doubtless, if, that) (not), + but, either, + except, + more(-over if, than), neither, nevertheless, nor, oh that, or, + save (only, -ing), seeing, since, sith, + surely (no more, none, not), though, + of a truth, + unless, + verily, when, whereas, whether, while, + yet.

h519.definition: apparently a primitive word; a maid-servant or female slave; (hand-) bondmaid(-woman), maid(-servant).

h520.definition: prolonged from {{h517}}; properly, a mother (i.e. unit of measure, or the fore-arm (below the elbow), i.e. a cubit; also a door-base (as a bond of the entrance); cubit, + hundred (by exchange for {{h3967}}), measure, post.

h522.definition: the same as {{h520}}; Ammah, a hill in Palestine; Ammah.

h523.definition: from the same as {{h517}}; a collection, i.e. community of persons; nation, people.

h525.definition: from {{h539}}, probably in the sense of training; like {{h542}}; skilled, i.e. an architect; one brought up.

h526.definition: the same as {{h525}}; Amon, the name of three Israelites; Amon.

h527.definition: a variation for {{h1995}}; a throng of people; multitude.

h528.definition: of Egyptian derivation; used only as an adjunct of {{h4996}}; Amon (i.e. Ammon or Amn), a deity of Egypt; multitude, populous.

h529.definition: from {{h539}}; established, i.e. (figuratively) trusty; also (abstractly) trustworthiness; faith(-ful), truth.

h530.definition: or (shortened) אֱמֻנָה; feminine of {{h529}}; literally firmness; figuratively security; morally fidelity; faith(-ful, -ly, -ness, (man)), set office, stability, steady, truly, truth, verily.

h531.definition: from {{h553}}; strong; Amots, an Israelite; Amoz.

h532.definition: an abbreviated form for {{h526}}; Ami, an Israelite; Ami.

h533.definition: or (shortened) אַמִּץ; from {{h553}}; strong or (abstractly) strength; courageous, mighty, strong (one).

h534.definition: apparently from {{h559}} (in the sense of self-exaltation); a summit (of a tree or mountain); bough, branch.

h535.definition: a primitive root; to droop; by implication to be sick, to mourn; languish, be weak, wax feeble.

h538.definition: from {{h517}}; gathering-spot; Amam, a place in Palestine; Amam.

h539.definition: a primitive root; (Isaiah 30:21; interchangeable with {{h541}}, to go to the right hand); properly, to build up or support; to foster as a parent or nurse; figuratively to render (or be) firm or faithful, to trust or believe, to be permanent or quiet; morally to be true or certain; hence, assurance, believe, bring up, establish,   fail, be faithful (of long continuance, stedfast, sure, surely, trusty, verified), nurse, (-ing father), (put), trust, turn to the right.

h541.definition: denominative from {{h3225}}; to take the right hand road; turn to the right. See {{h539}}.

h542.definition: from {{h539}} (in the sense of training); an expert; cunning workman.

h543.definition: from {{h539}}; sure; abstract, faithfulness; adverb, truly; Amen, so be it, truth.

h545.definition: feminine of {{h544}} (in the specific sense of training); tutelage; brought up.

h546.definition: feminine form of {{h544}} (in its usual sense); adverb, surely; indeed.

h547.definition: feminine active participle of {{h544}} (in the original sense of supporting); a column; pillar.

h548.definition: feminine of {{h543}}; something fixed, i.e. a covenant. an allowance; certain portion, sure.

h549.definition: the same as {{h548}}; Amanah, a mountain near Damascus; Amana.

h550.definition: or אֲמִינוֹן; from {{h539}}; faithful; Amnon (or Aminon), a son of David; Amnon.

h551.definition: adverb from {{h544}}; verily; indeed, no doubt, surely, (it is, of a) true(-ly, -th).

h552.definition: an orthographical variation of {{h551}}; in (very) deed; of a surety.

h553.definition: a primitive root; to be alert, physically (on foot) or mentally (in courage); confirm, be courageous (of good courage, stedfastly minded, strong, stronger), establish, fortify, harden, increase, prevail, strengthen (self), make strong (obstinate, speed).

h554.definition: probably from {{h553}}; of a strong color, i.e. red (others fleet); bay.

h557.definition: from {{h553}}; strong; Amtsi, an Israelite; Amzi.

h558.definition: or אֲמַצְיָהוּ; from {{h553}} and {{h3050}}; strength of Jah; Amatsjah, the name of four Israelites; Amaziah.

h559.definition: a primitive root; to say (used with great latitude); answer, appoint, avouch, bid, boast self, call, certify, challenge, charge,   (at the, give) command(-ment), commune, consider, declare, demand, × desire, determine, × expressly, × indeed, × intend, name, × plainly, promise, publish, report, require, say, speak (against, of), × still, × suppose, talk, tell, term, × that is, × think, use (speech), utter, × verily, × yet.

h560.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h559}}; command, declare, say, speak, tell.

h561.definition: from {{h559}}; something said; answer, × appointed unto him, saying, speech, word.

h562.definition: the same as {{h561}}; promise, speech, thing, word.

h563.definition: (Aramaic) perhaps from {{h560}} (in the sense of bringing forth); a lamb; lamb.

h564.definition: from {{h559}}; talkative; Immer, the name of five Israelites; Immer.

h565.definition: or אֶמְרָה; feminine of {{h561}}, and meaning the same; commandment, speech, word.

h566.definition: from {{h564}}; Imri, the name of two Israelites; Imri.

h567.definition: probably a patronymic from an unused name derived from {{h559}} in the sense of publicity, i.e. prominence; thus, a mountaineer; an Emorite, one of the Canaanitish tribes; Amorite.

h568.definition: or prolonged אֲמַרְיָהוּ; from {{h559}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has said (i.e. promised); Amarjah, the name of nine Israelites; Amariah.

h569.definition: of uncertain (perhaps foreign) derivation; Amraphel, a king of Shinar; Amraphel.

h570.definition: time past, i.e.; yesterday or last night; former time, yesterday(-night)

h571.definition: contracted from {{h539}}; stability; (figuratively) certainty, truth, trustworthiness; assured(-ly), establishment, faithful, right, sure, true (-ly, -th), verity.

h572.definition: from {{h4969}}; properly, something expansive, i.e. a bag; sack.

h573.definition: from {{h571}}; veracious; Amittai, an Israelite; Amittai.

h574.definition: (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of {{h4975}}; well-loined (i.e. burly) or mighty; terrible.

h575.definition: or אָנָה; contracted from {{h370}}; where?; hence, whither?, when?; also hither and thither; any (no) whither, now, where, whither(-soever).

h576.definition: (Aramaic) or אֲנָה; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h589}}; I; I, as for me.

h577.definition: or אָנָּה; apparent contracted from {{h160}} and {{h4994}}; oh now!; I (me) beseech (pray) thee, O.

h578.definition: a primitive root; to groan; lament, mourn.

h579.definition: a primitive root (perhaps rather identical with {{h578}} through the idea of contraction in anguish); to approach; hence, to meet in various senses; befall, deliver, happen, seek a quarrel.

h581.definition: (Aramaic) or (feminine) אִנִּיןlemma אֵנִּין first vowel, corrected to אִנִּין; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h1992}}; they; × are, them, these.

h582.definition: from {{h605}}; properly, a mortal (and thus differing from the more dignified {{h120}}); hence, a man in general (singly or collectively); another, × (blood-) thirsty, certain, chap(-man); divers, fellow, × in the flower of their age, husband, (certain, mortal) man, people, person, servant, some (× of them),   stranger, those,   their trade. It is often unexpressed in the English versions, especially when used in apposition with another word. Compare {{h376}}.

h583.definition: the same as {{h582}}; Enosh, a son of Seth; Enos.

h584.definition: a primitive root; to sigh; groan, mourn, sigh.

h586.definition: (Aramaic) or אֲנַחְנָה; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h587}}; we; we.

h587.definition: apparently from {{h595}}; we; ourselves, us, we.

h588.definition: probably from the same root as {{h5170}}; a gorge or narrow pass; Anacharath, a place in Palestine; Anaharath.

h589.definition: contracted from {{h595}}; I; I, (as for) me, mine, myself, we, × which, × who.

h590.definition: probably from {{h579}} (in the sense of conveyance); a ship or (collectively) a fleet; galley, navy (of ships).

h593.definition: from {{h578}} and {{h5971}}; groaning of (the) people; Aniam, an Israelite; Aniam.

h594.definition: probably from an unused root meaning to be narrow; according to most a plumb-line, and to others a hook; plumb-line

h595.definition: sometimes, אָנֹכִי; a primitive pronoun; I; I, me, × which.

h596.definition: a primitive root; to mourn, i.e. complain; complain.

h598.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h597}}; figuratively, to distress; trouble.

h599.definition: a primitive root; to breathe hard, i.e. be enraged; be angry (displeased).

h600.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h639}} (only in the plural as a singular); the face; face, visage.
